          "title": "Sovereign timing — the Lamb dies on Passover",
          "body": "John emphasizes three calendrical markers: *day of Preparation for the Passover* (19:14, 31, 42), *the sixth hour* (19:14), and *that Sabbath was a high day* (19:31). The Mishnah (*Pesachim* 5) records that the Passover lambs were inspected and slaughtered in the Temple courts between roughly noon and 3 PM on Preparation Day. John times the death of Jesus to that very window. The Lamb of God (1:29) dies as the Passover lambs are dying. This is not coincidence; this is the Father's calendar. Centuries of Passover lambs were rehearsals; this is the substance."
