          "body": "The single most important word in the chapter is the perfect-tense *tetelestai* (19:30) — *it stands completed, it has been finished, with abiding result*. Twice in two verses John uses the same root: Jesus knew all things *had already been accomplished* (28, *tetelestai*), and then cried *it is finished* (30, *tetelestai*). This is not a sigh of relief. It was the word merchants stamped on a paid bill — *paid in full*. It was the word a workman used when his commission was complete. The atoning work the Father gave the Son to do (17:4) is consummated. Nothing remains for any sinner to add; nothing remains for any priest to repeat (Hebrews 10:11-14). The verb is the chapter's gospel anchor."
